clinical_particulars.therapeutic_indications: Indicated when parenteral therapy is necessary for inotropic support in the short term treatment of patients with cardiac decompensation due to depressed contractility resulting either from organic heart disease or from cardiac surgical procedures

contraindications.pharmacodynamics: Dobutamine is a direct acting inotropic agent whose primary activity results from stimulation of the beta adrenoceptors of the heart while producing comparatively mild chronotropic hypertensive arrhythmogenic and vasodilative effects Dobutamine acts primarily on beta 1 adrenergic receptors with negligible effects on beta 2 or alpha receptors It does not cause the release of endogenous norepinephrine as does dopamine
